definitions.definition: A blade mounted to the end of a long gun , originally with a handle inserted into the bore , now usually attached underbarrel .
A pin which plays in and out of holes made to receive it, and which thus serves to engage or disengage parts of the machinery .

main_definition: ( military ) A blade mounted to the end of a long gun , originally with a handle inserted into the bore , now usually attached underbarrel .
